verbose_text: To explore whether ovariectomy induced declines of proliferation, adhesion, and osteogenic differentiation in rBMSCs would be reversed by Cal administration (10 -9 M) and whether this treatment was associated with CaSR activation, we examined the levels of CaSR, PCNA, cyclin D1, and ICAM-1 as well as the ALP activities in OVX-rBMSCs administered Cal treatment.
evidence: levels of CaSR, PCNA, cyclin D1, and ICAM-1
